(a) The schematic of the shear test, showing the loading direction is perpendicular to the direction of the machined grooves, (b) the relationship between the shear strength and the processing speed, which first increases with the processing speed and then decreases, (c) the fracture morphology of the surface machined zirconia/Ti6Al4V brazing joint, (d) the hardness distribution across the interface in the joint, (e) the morphology of a failed surface micromachined YSZ/Ti6Al4V brazing joint.
